// Man page for pRoot
manPRoot="PROOT(1)                         X Shell Manual                         PROOT(1)

<b>NAME</b>
    proot - Automated root shell and pivot

<b>SYNOPSIS</b>
    <b>proot</b> [<b>-y</b>]

<b>DESCRIPTION</b>
    Automated privilege escalation and directory pivot utility. Secures root
    shell access and automatically pivots framework into compromised user home
    directory. Streamlines post-exploitation workflow. Only compatible with
    shell objects. Optional confirmation bypass via <b>-y</b> or the
    <b>yes</b> command.

<b>OPTIONS</b>
    <b>proot</b>
        Get root shell and pivot to user home
        Prompts for confirmation

    <b>proot -y</b>
        Skip confirmation prompts (or run <b>yes</b> first)
        Immediate execution

<b>EXAMPLE:</b>
    <color=#e4ff34># Standard Usage</color>
    <b>proot</b>
        Get root and pivot with prompts

    <color=#e4ff34># Automated Workflows</color>
    <b>proot -y</b>
        No prompts, quick execution

    <b>yes</b>
    <b>proot</b>
        Same via session auto-yes

    <color=#e4ff34># Exploitation Workflow</color>
    <b>scan -l</b>
        Get shell access first

    <b>proot</b>
        Escalate and pivot

    <b>cdl /root</b>
        Explore root directory

<b>SEE ALSO</b>
    <b>sudo</b>, <b>su</b>, <b>passwd</b>, <b>pivot</b>, <b>yes</b>"